      "role": "user",
      "content": "sounds good, let's see what you got. the most important parts are the login flow (user enters creds -> hits submit -> redirected to dashboard) and the main chart rendering on the dashboard. \n\nhere is a snippet of the current failing test for the login:\n\n```javascript\ntest('user can login', async ({ page }) => {\n  await page.goto('/login');\n  await page.fill('#username', 'testuser');\n  await page.fill('#password', 'password123');\n  await page.click('#login-btn');\n  // THIS IS WHERE IT FAILS: it times out waiting for the dashboard to load\n  await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard'); \n  const welcomeMsg = page.locator('#welcome-message');\n  await expect(welcomeMsg).toBeVisible();\n});\n```\n\ncan you rewrite this and some tests for the dashboard charts so they are \"rock solid\" and won't fail the CI build even if the backend is being slow or the charts take a second to render?",
